  "stac_version": "1.1.0",
  "description": "## Kd Ocean Colour Blue by Sentinel-5P TROPOMI (Daily)\nThe Kd Ocean Colour (blue) product provides the diffuse attenuation coefficient (Kd) in the short blue wavelength range (390–423 nm), quantifying **how sunlight is absorbed and scattered in the upper ocean layer**.\n\nData are essential for monitoring ocean optical properties, phytoplankton, and marine ecosystem health.\n\n#### About the dataset\n- Kd-blue measures the attenuation of downwelling plane irradiance in the ocean’s first optical depth.\n- The product is generated using Differential Optical Absorption Spectroscopy (DOAS) adapted to oceanic applications (PhytoDOAS), with retrievals converted into physical Kd values using radiative transfer look-up tables. Only high-quality measurements (qa_value == 1.0) are used in the final gridded product.\n\n#### Use cases\nKd-blue measurements are particularly useful for:\n- Studying light penetration and ocean color dynamics.\n- Ocean biogeochemistry and primary productivity modeling.\n- Monitoring phytoplankton blooms and water quality.\n- Climate studies related to ocean radiative transfer and carbon cycling.\n\n\n",
